The '''Gwawaenuk Tribe''', or '''Gwawa<U+02BC>enux<U+0331>w''' is a [[band government]] of the [[Kwakwaka'wakw]] people located in the [[Queen Charlotte Strait]] region of the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region of British Columbia]], [[Canada]].<ref name="Gwawaenuk">{{cite web |year= 2009 |url = http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/FNMain.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=627&lang=e|title = Gwawaenuk Tribe |work= [[Government of Canada]]|publisher = [[Executive Council of British Columbia]]| accessdate = July 26, 2009 | last= |quote=}}</ref>  The Gwawaenuk Tribe has no year-round road access to a service centre and being about 160&nbsp;km to 240&nbsp;km from the nearest service centre.<ref name="Gwawaenuk"/>

== Language ==
As of 2012, about half the tribe speaks the [[Kwak'wala]] langage.<ref name = "languagemap">{{Cite web
| title = Gwawa<U+02BC>enux<U+0331>w
| work = First Peoples' Language Map of British Columbia
| accessdate = 2012-11-08
| url = http://maps.fphlcc.ca/gwawaenuk
}}</ref> The tribe's dialect is called "Gwawaenuk."<ref>{{Cite web
| title = Language Needs Assessment: Gwawaenuk Tribe Kwakwaka'wakw Nation
| accessdate = 2012-11-08
| url = http://maps.fphlcc.ca/node/1245
}}</ref> 

==Demographics==
First nation number 627 with 39 members.<ref name="Gwawaenuk"/> It is one of about 175 Aboriginal Communities in Canada that is [[off-the-grid]].<ref>{{Cite web
| title = Off-Grid Communities
| work = Aboriginal Affairs and Northern Development Canada
| accessdate = 2012-11-08
| url = http://www.aadnc-aandc.gc.ca/eng/1314295992771/1314296121126
}}</ref>

